title: Video: Possible kidnapping victim jumps out of car
text:
BRIDGEPORT, CT (WABC/CNN) - Disturbing video shows a teenager escape an apparent kidnapping.
Police are on the lookout for the car and its driver. In the video, someone can be seen falling out of the passenger side.
The 17-year-old girl told police she was walking to school when the driver of Toyota lured her into the car.
Once she was inside, she said she was assaulted by a woman who appeared to be in her 40s. The teenager was able to jump out of the moving car.
